---
import OldWebLayout from '@/layouts/OldWebLayout.astro';
---
<OldWebLayout title="about VOID" section="voidshell">
  <div class="status-strip">
    <span>void</span>
    <span>about</span>
    <span>not corporate, not affiliated</span>
    <span><a href="/void">return to portal</a></span>
  </div>

  <h1>About VOID</h1>

  <p class="tagline-block">
    VOID is a user-submitted map of the parts of the internet OmniShift would prefer you not visit.
    We do not endorse anything here. Most things here do not endorse us either.
  </p>

  <section class="old-shell">
    <div class="old-header">What this is</div>
    <div class="old-body">
      <p>
        VOID indexes pages OmniShift removed, never indexed, or pretended weren't there.
        Some of these pages are real. Some are rumored. Some are filed under
        <i>"the directory may have changed its mind."</i>
      </p>
      <p>
        We don't moderate by topic. We moderate by whether the page belongs to the room.
        If the room admits it, it stays. If the room laughs at it, it stays. If the room
        flags it, the directory moves a door.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="old-shell">
    <div class="old-header">What this isn't</div>
    <div class="old-body">
      <ul>
        <li>A search engine. (Search bar works. Results are negotiable.)</li>
        <li>A social network. (No likes, followers, or feeds. Sign someone's guestbook.)</li>
        <li>A marketplace. (Real money begins at <a href="/rack">The Rack</a>. Everywhere else is bit.)</li>
        <li>OmniShift property. They are aware. They have not commented.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="old-shell">
    <div class="old-header">House rules</div>
    <div class="old-body">
      <p>
        See <a href="/house-rules">House Rules</a>. They apply here, in the lot, and at any
        table that pretends to be a table.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <p class="memo-box">
    Tip jar: empty. Bartender: also empty. Tip the bartender anyway.
  </p>
</OldWebLayout>
